# Homework Helper

A comprehensive Flutter homework management app with AI study buddy, social features, and gamification.

## Social System — Firestore Security Rules

The social features store data in Firestore. Below are **recommended** security rules.
These are not enforced by the app code alone; add them in the Firebase console under
Firestore > Rules to enforce privacy on the backend.

```javascript
rules_version = '2';
service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {

    // User documents: owner can read/write; others can read only public fields.
    match /users/{uid} {
      allow read: if request.auth != null;
      allow write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == uid;

      // Accepted friends sub-collection
      match /friends/{friendUid} {
        allow read: if request.auth != null &&
          (request.auth.uid == uid || request.auth.uid == friendUid);
        allow write: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == uid;
      }

      // Incoming friend-request sub-collection (new model)
      match /friendRequests/{requestId} {
        // The target user (uid) can read their own incoming requests.
        // The sender (fromUid in the document) can write (create).
        allow read: if request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == uid;
        allow create: if request.auth != null &&
          request.resource.data.fromUid == request.auth.uid;
        allow delete: if request.auth != null &&
          (request.auth.uid == uid ||
           request.auth.uid == resource.data.fromUid);
      }
    }

    // Global friend-requests collection (legacy / dual-write model)
    match /friend_requests/{requestId} {
      allow read: if request.auth != null &&
        (resource.data.from == request.auth.uid ||
         resource.data.to   == request.auth.uid);
      allow create: if request.auth != null &&
        request.resource.data.from == request.auth.uid;
      allow update, delete: if request.auth != null &&
        (resource.data.from == request.auth.uid ||
         resource.data.to   == request.auth.uid);
    }

    // Username → UID mapping (usernames collection)
    match /usernames/{handle} {
      allow read: if request.auth != null;
      // Only the owning user (or anyone claiming a free handle) may write.
      allow write: if request.auth != null &&
        (!resource.exists || resource.data.uid == request.auth.uid);
    }
  }
}
```

> **Privacy enforcement note:** Profile-visibility and friend-request privacy settings
> are enforced in the UI. For full backend enforcement, extend the rules above to
> check `users/{uid}.profileVisibility` and `users/{uid}.friendRequestsPrivacy` before
> allowing reads/writes to the relevant documents.
